text: San Jose College, Durango, Spain, is a school begun in 1885. It includes infant through baccalaureate education and fosters the Basque culture and language, while also teaching Spanish and English. ==References== Category:Jesuit secondary schools in Spain Category:Catholic schools in Spain Category:Secondary schools in Spain Category:Jesuit secondary schools Category:Educational institutions established in 1885
title: San Jose College, Durango
